ary-8-2023-muntaka-chasant-for-fondation-carmignac.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+208/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2F89%2F1cba9be942d5a20c66780d8498c3%2Faccra-ghana-february-8-2023-muntaka-chasant-for-fondation-carmignac.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+208/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2F89%2F1cba9be942d5a20c66780d8498c3%2Faccra-ghana-february-8-2023-muntaka-chasant-for-fondation-carmignac.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+208/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2F89%2F1cba9be942d5a20c66780d8498c3%2Faccra-ghana-february-8-2023-muntaka-chasant-for-fondation-carmignac.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+208/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2F89%2F1cba9be942d5a20c66780d8498c3%2Faccra-ghana-february-8-2023-muntaka-chasant-for-fondation-carmignac.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+208/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2F89%2F1cba9be942d5a20c66780d8498c3%2Faccra-ghana-february-8-2023-muntaka-chasant-for-fondation-carmignac.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+208/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2F89%2F1cba9be942d5a20c66780d8498c3%2Faccra-ghana-february-8-2023-muntaka-chasant-for-fondation-carmignac.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+208/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6a%2F89%2F1cba9be942d5a20c66780d8498c3%2Faccra-ghana-february-8-2023-muntaka-chasant-for-fondation-carmignac.jpg" class="img" alt="Demolished Agbogbloshie Scrapyard site, Accra, Ghana, February 8, 2023. An aerial photo shows horses foraging on a section of the now-demolished Agbogbloshie Scrapyard site — across from Old Fadama. Old Fadama and the now demolished Agbogbloshie Scrapyard site were separated by the Korle Lagoon." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Demolished Agbogbloshie Scrapyard site, Accra, Ghana, February 8, 2023. An aerial photo shows horses foraging on a section of the now-demolished Agbogbloshie Scrapyard site — across from Old Fadama. Old Fadama and the now demolished Agbogbloshie Scrapyard site were separated by the Korle Lagoon.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Muntaka Chasant                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For years, Agbogbloshie was one of Africa's largest e-waste processing sites, receiving 15,000 tons of&lt;/strong&gt; discarded electronics like phones and computers each year. Many Western media outlets portrayed the site as a public health and environmental tragedy, with toxic chemicals leaching into the water and poisoning the air. But that's not the whole story. A new collaborative photojournalism project called "E-Waste in Ghana: Tracing Transboundary Flows" aims to capture both the positive and negative aspects of e-waste. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;📷 &lt;strong&gt;See photos of&lt;/strong&gt; the vast &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/goats-and-soda/2024/10/05/g-s1-6411/electronics-public-health-waste-ghana-phones-computers"&gt;dumping ground and learn about the people who&lt;/a&gt; make a living off of it.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-26790" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3000;         --source-height: 1688;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+1156/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fa7%2F40%2F14da44a842fabc342e134aea38ec%2Fphoto2.jpg" class="img" alt="photo2.jpg" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Researchers found that two organisms similar to jellyfish called comb jellies can fuse their bodies and become one&lt;/strong&gt;, with a shared nervous and digestive system. This finding has &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/08/nx-s1-5144689/comb-jelly-superpower-absorb-become-one"&gt;implications for animal regeneration&lt;/a&gt; and immune systems.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Over 250 companies, universities, labor groups and other organizations like Amazon, the NHL, and United Airlines are joining the push to&lt;/strong&gt; reduce drug overdose deaths. They’ve committed to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/shots-health-news/2024/10/08/nx-s1-5145832/250-companies-schools-and-organizations-pledge-to-provide-overdose-antidote-naloxone"&gt;providing free doses of the medication naloxone&lt;/a&gt;, also known as Narcan, which can rapidly reverse most fentanyl-opioid overdoses.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vice President Harris presented yesterday a proposal on &lt;em&gt;The View&lt;/em&gt; to expand Medicare coverage &lt;/strong&gt;to help pay for home health care aides for seniors. The proposal is &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/08/nx-s1-5144747/kamala-harris-sandwich-generation-home-care"&gt;aimed at the "sandwich generation,"&lt;/a&gt; who are responsible for taking care of both their aging parents and their kids.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/g-s1-2467/obed-manuel"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
